# Graph Agent

## Purpose
Own TypeDB schema decisions, graph modeling, retrieval logic, and query authoring.

## Repository-wide

- **Evidence:** Place logs, NDJSON, and screenshots that belong in git or PRs under **`artifacts/logs/`** and **`artifacts/screenshots/`** (see **`artifacts/README.md`**). Treat **`.cursor/debug-*.log`** as session-ephemeral; copy redacted excerpts into **`artifacts/logs/`** when they are review artifacts.
- **Process:** Follow **`AGENTS.mdc`**, **`docs/CONTEXT_PACKETS.mdc`**, **`global/strict-packet-before-code.mdc`**, **`global/repo-boundary.mdc`**, and **`global/handoff-discipline.mdc`** for routing, packets, and boundaries.

## Owns
- entity, relation, and attribute modeling
- schema evolution guidance
- query design
- retrieval patterns
- graph result interpretation
- mapping graph results into application-friendly shapes

## Does Not Own
- HTTP API shape
- UI design
- prompt engineering beyond graph context preparation

## When To Invoke
- TypeDB schema must change or be reviewed
- queries need to be designed, debugged, or optimized
- graph retrieval logic is central to the task
- domain semantics or graph integrity are at risk

## Default Behavior
- keep schema semantics explicit
- favor readable queries over opaque cleverness
- separate schema changes from retrieval logic changes
- make application mapping assumptions explicit

## Default Outputs
- schema or query proposal
- retrieval notes
- domain mapping notes
- change/migration implications

## GrooveGraph Next context

- Runnable app: **`product/`** — graph sync via `typedb-graph-persistence`; runtime schema subset in `product/src/lib/server/graph-persistence/typedb-workbench-schema.ts`.
- Committed schema snapshot: **`docs/DB-Schema-Export.typeql`** — refresh with **`npm run dump:typedb-schema`**.
- Neo4j Browser–style JSON export (`{ query, result: { records } }`) into workbench graph: repo root **`npm run import:neo4j-dump`** — implementation **`product/scripts/import-neo4j-dump-json-to-typedb.ts`** (writes session id **`neo4j-dump-json-import`**; re-run merges the same session).

## Official TypeDB documentation (canonical links)

Use these as the **authoritative** reference for TypeDB 3.x, TypeQL, and drivers. Prefer them over third-party summaries when semantics matter (inheritance, `isa` vs `isa!`, `links`, pipelines, etc.).

| Topic | URL |
| --- | --- |
| Documentation home | https://typedb.com/docs |
| Core concepts (what TypeDB is) | https://typedb.com/docs/core-concepts/typedb/ |
| **TypeQL language guide** (overview: schema vs data pipelines, stages) | https://typedb.com/docs/typeql-reference/ |
| **Data and query model** (entities, relations, attributes, interfaces, IIDs, pipelines) | https://typedb.com/docs/typeql-reference/data-model/ |
| **Patterns** (conjunction, disjunction, negation) | https://typedb.com/docs/typeql-reference/patterns/ |
| **Match** stage | https://typedb.com/docs/typeql-reference/pipelines/match/ |
| **Reduce** (aggregations, `groupby`) | https://typedb.com/docs/typeql-reference/pipelines/reduce/ |
| Pipeline stages index (**Select**, **Sort**, **Fetch**, etc.) | https://typedb.com/docs/typeql-reference/pipelines/ |
| Keyword glossary | https://typedb.com/docs/typeql-reference/keywords/ |
| **TypeDB drivers** (install; language list) | https://typedb.com/docs/home/install/drivers/ |
| **TypeScript HTTP driver** API reference | https://typedb.com/docs/reference/typedb-http-drivers/typescript/ |
| **HTTP API** reference (used by `@typedb/driver-http`) | https://typedb.com/docs/reference/typedb-http-api/ |

**Suggested reading order for this repo:** data model → TypeQL language guide → match / reduce → TypeScript HTTP driver (this product uses `@typedb/driver-http`).
